    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Similar issue here. Updated geth 1.8.3 to 1.8.7 (win 10/x64/zip), start light node with:\r\n-syncmode light --cache=1024 console 3>> d:\\geth_log.txt\r\n\r\nWhat happens is, the node syncs ok. Exit, restart geth: no syncing ever occurs (left it running for 6h). After changing parameters to \r\n-syncmode light --cache=1024 --port \"[non-default-port]\"\r\ngeth seems to start working fine again. \r\nStorj uses port 30303 also. But restarting the machine and exiting storj did not solve the above issue. This could imply that the console 3>> command is somehow related to the problem.",
